# Project: DDPM (Dylan DiBona Property Management)
# Description: A rental property finance tracker and automated consultant.

## User Persona
- Owner of multiple rental properties.
- Not a developer. Prioritize code stability, clear error messages, and simple instructions.

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: Next.js 14 (App Router), React, Lucide React (icons).
- Styling: Tailwind CSS.
- UI Library: Shadcn/UI (Use npx shadcn@latest add [component]).
- Database: PostgreSQL (via Prisma ORM).
- Authentication: Clerk (clerk.com).
- AI: OpenAI API (gpt-4o) for document analysis.
- Storage/Ingestion: Google Drive API (Service Account).

## Design System
- Vibe: Super clean, "CFO dashboard", black and white base.
- Colors:
  - Background: White (#ffffff) or extremely light gray (#f8fafc).
  - Text: Slate 900 (#0f172a).
  - Accents: Dark Blue (#1e3a8a) and Deep Purple (#581c87).
- Typography: Inter or Geist Sans. Clean, readable, professional.

## Core Features
1. Dashboard: High-level metrics (Year to Date Income, Expenses, Net).
2. Documents: List of files pulled from Google Drive.
3. Analysis: AI extraction of data from PDFs (Date, Amount, Category, Vendor, Flagged Issues).
4. Tax Prep: "Deduction Hunter" mode.

## Rules
- When generating code, always ensure it is compatible with Vercel deployment.
- Use environment variables for all secrets (DATABASE_URL, OPENAI_API_KEY, GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS).
- If a complex setup is required (like Google Cloud Console), provide a step-by-step checklist for the user.